        B10 | THE STRAITS TIMES THURSDAY, SEPTEMBER 10, 2020 | | | OBITUARIES FOR BOOKINGS AND ENQUIRIES 1800-289-9988 6319-5192 or ML LOGISTICS SERVICES 10th Anniversar­y In Loving Memory Of We were greatly saddened to learn of the passing of Mr YC Chang, Chairman Emeritus of Pacific Internatio­nal Lines (PIL), Singapore. LIM MENG LONG, DACKSON Age: 56 Passed away peacefully on 8 September 2020. Dearly missed and fondly remembered by loved ones. Boo Mui Lee Wife: PETER TAN ENG SIAN Brothers: Sister-in-law: Lim Meng Fong, Kelvin Lim Meng Shyan, Jeremy Liu Pau Wah called home to be with the Lord on 10 September 2010 Sister: A good and honest life is a blessed memorial ... Proverbs 10:7 Lim Meng Horng, Jean Nephew: Niece: Lim Dao Jun Lim Jing Dearly missed and always cherished by wife Alice, children, grandchild­ren and great-grandchild­ren And all relatives and friends. Wake is held at
Blk 751 Choa Chu Kang North 5, Singapore 680751 Cortege will leave on 11 September 2020, Friday at 9am for Mandai Crematoriu­m Hall 1 for cremation at 10.05am We wish to extend to his son SS Teo and the whole of Mr Chang’s family our deepest sympathy and condolence­s on their sad loss. Mr Chang was indeed a remarkable man who achieved considerab­le success during his lifetime. Establishi­ng PIL in 1967, he built the company up over the years to reach the world’s top ten ranking in the liner industry. 11th Anniversar­y In loving Memory of Aum Shanti Aum TWENTIETH ANNIVERSAR­Y Mr Chang loved his work and his company and we know that he was attending the office daily up until just recently, a remarkable achievemen­t for someone of 102 years of age. Sarangapan­y s/o T.Maruthan @ Bani Our thoughts and prayers are with Mr Chang’s family at this time. Departed - 12th Sep 2009 Late wife - Kamachy d/o Samiappan Chettiar (deceased) Departed - 14th Feb 2012 Cecilia Eckelmann-Battistell­o on behalf of Contship Italia Group You may be gone from my sight but You’ll always remain in our thoughts Sadly missed & always remembered by :
Geetha
